.TH "ntfs_set_volume_flags" 9 "ntfs_set_volume_flags" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ntfs_set_volume_flags \- set bits in the volume information flags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ntfs_set_volume_flags
.BI "(ntfs_volume *vol "  ","
.BI "VOLUME_FLAGS flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vol" 12
ntfs volume on which to modify the flags
.IP "flags" 12
flags to set on the volume
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the bits in \fIflags\fP in the volume information flags on the volume \fIvol\fP.

Return 0 on success and -errno on error.
